1
00:00:02,919 --> 00:00:05,964
- Previously on "Friends"...
- I don't feel like I have a girlfriend.

2
00:00:06,214 --> 00:00:09,217
You want me to quit my job so you
can feel like you have a girlfriend?

3
00:00:09,467 --> 00:00:11,302
- Is this about Mark?
- Oh, my God.

4
00:00:11,553 --> 00:00:13,888
- Okay, it's not.
- Oh, my God.

5
00:00:14,139 --> 00:00:16,224
I cannot keep having this
fight with you!

6
00:00:16,474 --> 00:00:18,685
Maybe we should just take a break.

7
00:00:18,935 --> 00:00:21,021
Fine. You're right.
Let's take a break.

8
00:00:21,271 --> 00:00:25,025
Let's get some frozen yogurt
or something.

9
00:00:25,275 --> 00:00:28,653
A break from us.

10
00:00:29,404 --> 00:00:32,991
Then we had this big fight,
and I said I wanted to take a break.

11
00:00:33,241 --> 00:00:34,868
I don't want to take a break.

12
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:36,202
This is crazy.

13
00:00:36,453 --> 00:00:38,163
{y:i}Can't we work on this?

14
00:00:38,413 --> 00:00:39,622
What do you want to drink?

15
00:00:39,873 --> 00:00:42,250
Who's that?

16
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:44,002
Nobody.

17
00:00:44,252 --> 00:00:45,045
Is that Mark?

18
00:00:45,295 --> 00:00:46,588
Honey, look, he just...

19
00:00:46,838 --> 00:00:49,299
Yeah. Got it!

20
00:00:49,549 --> 00:00:52,552
Hey, come dance.
What, are you married?

21
00:00:52,802 --> 00:00:56,014
Because that's okay.

22
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:12,947
How was the big anniversary dinner?

23
00:01:13,198 --> 00:01:16,993
Well, we never actually got to dinner.

24
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:19,704
Nice.

25
00:01:20,288 --> 00:01:21,998
We kind of broke up instead.

26
00:01:22,248 --> 00:01:24,709
What?

27
00:01:26,836 --> 00:01:28,880
My God!
It's on the ceiling!

28
00:01:29,130 --> 00:01:30,173
That's okay.

29
00:01:30,423 --> 00:01:32,634
This is more important than fruit...

30
00:01:32,884 --> 00:01:35,762
...on my ceiling.

31
00:01:35,970 --> 00:01:36,805
You broke up?

32
00:01:37,055 --> 00:01:41,226
Yeah, but it's okay because
when Ross left, Mark came over.

33
00:01:41,476 --> 00:01:43,978
- Oh, no! You and Mark?
- It's okay. Calm down.

34
00:01:44,229 --> 00:01:45,605
Mark and I talked...

35
00:01:45,855 --> 00:01:50,318
...and I realized how much
I love your stupid brother.

36
00:01:50,568 --> 00:01:55,323
We got our problems,
but I really wanna make it work.

37
00:02:11,214 --> 00:02:13,800
Morning!

38
00:02:17,595 --> 00:02:20,890
The One the Morning After

39
00:03:09,481 --> 00:03:13,526
{y:i}It's me. I've been trying
{y:i}to reach you all night. I feel awful.

40
00:03:13,777 --> 00:03:16,821
{y:i}There's nothing between me and Mark.

41
00:03:17,072 --> 00:03:21,993
{y:i}This whole breakup thing
{y:i}is just stupid.

42
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:24,829
{y:i}I'm sorry I put you through it.

43
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:28,917
{y:i}And I don't want to get
{y:i}back together over a machine.

44
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:30,627
{y:i}So I love you.

45
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:31,670
I love you.

46
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:35,256
{y:i}And you know what?
{y:i}I'm gonna go to bed now...

47
00:03:35,507 --> 00:03:41,846
{y:i}... but on my way to work tomorrow,
{y:i}I'll stop by around 8:30. Bye.

48
00:03:43,556 --> 00:03:44,891
Chloe, how's it coming?

49
00:03:45,141 --> 00:03:47,519
What kind of puppy do you think
I should get?

50
00:03:47,769 --> 00:03:49,813
Well, how about a big one?

51
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:52,524
- But my apartment's so...
- Then a small one.

52
00:03:52,774 --> 00:03:55,193
- We have to go.
- Wait! Where's my shoes?

53
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:58,071
You need shoes?

54
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:03,743
- Do I know why we're rushing?
- You know my girlfriend?

55
00:04:03,993 --> 00:04:06,996
It turns out that she wants
to get back together.

56
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:08,164
I found it!

57
00:04:08,415 --> 00:04:10,542
That's so great for you guys!

58
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:12,168
You must be so happy!

59
00:04:12,419 --> 00:04:16,840
Yes, I am. One of the many
things I'm feeling.

60
00:04:17,549 --> 00:04:21,886
- Good luck with your girlfriend.
- Thank you.

61
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:32,731
- You got my message?
- You are right on time!

62
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:35,275
So can I be your girlfriend again?

63
00:04:35,525 --> 00:04:38,528
Yes, you can. Very much.

64
00:04:45,535 --> 00:04:49,914
- Why are you mopping your ceiling?
- There's banana on it.

65
00:04:50,165 --> 00:04:54,753
I have the spirit of an
old Indian woman living in mine.

66
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:57,547
So, then, you know.

67
00:04:59,341 --> 00:05:01,509
The mailman was here,
so I brought your mail.

68
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:05,221
- Oh, good. Thanks.
- Now, what is Fabutech?

69
00:05:05,472 --> 00:05:08,141
Don't judge me too much, okay?

70
00:05:08,391 --> 00:05:11,770
I saw this infomercial,
and I swear I have never...

71
00:05:12,020 --> 00:05:14,230
...bought anything on TV before.

72
00:05:14,481 --> 00:05:16,775
Except for this mop.

73
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:19,444
But there was this amazing stuff
on leg-waxing...

74
00:05:19,694 --> 00:05:20,612
Waxine!

75
00:05:20,862 --> 00:05:22,238
Yes! Have you seen it?

76
00:05:22,489 --> 00:05:25,033
It's incredible!
I want to be a Waxine Girl!

77
00:05:25,283 --> 00:05:27,619
I know!

78
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:31,289
Do you think it really doesn't hurt?
How can they do that?

79
00:05:31,539 --> 00:05:35,210
Hello! Organic substances recently
discovered in the rain forest?

80
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:38,922
They have the best stuff in there.

81
00:05:39,172 --> 00:05:41,675
Oh, my God!

82
00:05:41,925 --> 00:05:44,052
Oh, my God!

83
00:05:44,302 --> 00:05:48,306
We figured when we couldn't find you,
you'd gone to make up with Rachel.

84
00:05:48,556 --> 00:05:52,227
Which is probably what
you should have done.

85
00:05:52,268 --> 00:05:54,688
You think?

86
00:05:54,771 --> 00:05:58,233
God, I'm in hell.
I mean, what am I gonna do?

87
00:05:58,483 --> 00:06:02,529
Rachel's all "I love you",
and all I can think about...

88
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:05,657
...is what is she gonna do
when I tell her what I did?

89
00:06:05,907 --> 00:06:09,536
First, we should address
the more important question...

90
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:12,747
...how dumb are you?

91
00:06:13,373 --> 00:06:17,210
Look, we're trying to
rebuild a relationship here, right?

92
00:06:17,460 --> 00:06:20,005
How can I do that
without being honest?

93
00:06:20,255 --> 00:06:23,508
I'm onboard about
the total-honesty thing. I am.

94
00:06:23,758 --> 00:06:27,554
Just not about stuff that's
gonna get you in trouble.

95
00:06:27,804 --> 00:06:30,890
He's right. Nobody benefits,
and you'll just hurt her.

96
00:06:31,141 --> 00:06:33,935
And there won't be a relationship
left to rebuild.

97
00:06:34,185 --> 00:06:35,103
Don't you think...

98
00:06:35,353 --> 00:06:38,815
If you have to tell her,
at least wait till the timing's right.

99
00:06:39,065 --> 00:06:42,610
And that's what deathbeds are for.

100
00:06:43,987 --> 00:06:46,072
- Yeah, okay.
- All right.

101
00:06:46,322 --> 00:06:52,370
Okay. Now, we just have to make sure
she doesn't find out some other way.

102
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:56,374
Did you think about the trail?

103
00:06:56,916 --> 00:06:59,336
What trail?

104
00:07:00,337 --> 00:07:01,921
From the woman
you did it with...

105
00:07:02,172 --> 00:07:05,967
...to the woman you hope
never finds out you did it!

106
00:07:06,217 --> 00:07:09,679
Always think about the trail!

107
00:07:09,929 --> 00:07:13,892
I don't think there's any trail.

108
00:07:14,184 --> 00:07:16,519
Chloe works with that guy, Isaac.

109
00:07:16,770 --> 00:07:20,857
Isaac's sister is Jasmine, who works
at the massage place with Phoebe.

110
00:07:21,107 --> 00:07:25,653
Phoebe is Rachel's friend,
and that's the trail! I did it!

111
00:07:26,988 --> 00:07:29,908
"After applying the Waxine
and linen strips to leg..."

112
00:07:30,158 --> 00:07:32,160
Did that!

113
00:07:32,410 --> 00:07:34,871
"Grasp the linen strip by its tab...

114
00:07:35,121 --> 00:07:39,542
...and pull it off in one quick,
pain-free motion."

115
00:07:42,545 --> 00:07:45,131
Was it not "pain-free"?

116
00:07:45,382 --> 00:07:47,217
No, it was pain-ful!

117
00:07:47,467 --> 00:07:52,597
My God, they should call it
"Pain-zine, now with a little wax."

118
00:07:52,681 --> 00:07:56,518
The girls on the commercial
don't seem to think it's that bad.

119
00:07:56,768 --> 00:08:01,439
Because their nerves are
deadened from being so stupid.

120
00:08:01,648 --> 00:08:07,404
But you know, if you don't
believe me, please, be my guest.

121
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:15,203
Now are you glad we didn't start
with the bikini strips?

122
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:21,418
Chloe, hi.

123
00:08:21,668 --> 00:08:24,546
Is this about me taking your watch?

124
00:08:24,796 --> 00:08:28,508
- You took my watch?
- I'm sorry. I do that.

125
00:08:28,758 --> 00:08:32,262
You keep it. Listen, did you
tell anyone about us?

126
00:08:32,512 --> 00:08:35,598
I feel like it really isn't
anybody's business.

127
00:08:35,849 --> 00:08:38,977
Exactly. So you didn't
mention anything to Isaac?

128
00:08:39,227 --> 00:08:44,441
- I tell Isaac everything.
- You do? Of course you do.

129
00:08:45,108 --> 00:08:48,319
Hi, Isaac.
You know, we haven't actually met.

130
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:51,656
You dog!

131
00:08:52,949 --> 00:08:57,370
Yes, I suppose I am a dog. But see,
I happen to have a girlfriend.

132
00:08:57,620 --> 00:08:59,831
Right. Rachel from the coffee place.

133
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:02,876
That's the one.
Listen, I don't want to hurt her.

134
00:09:03,126 --> 00:09:05,837
I know. It doesn't matter
how much we love them.

135
00:09:06,087 --> 00:09:10,175
Monogamy is too cruel a rule.

136
00:09:11,384 --> 00:09:14,971
Listen, can you keep this
information to yourself?

137
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:17,599
No problem.
We gotta look out for each other.

138
00:09:17,849 --> 00:09:21,144
We're the same, you and me.

139
00:09:22,771 --> 00:09:25,315
Actually, no, we're not.

140
00:09:25,565 --> 00:09:27,317
Yeah, we are.

141
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:29,277
No, we're not.

142
00:09:29,527 --> 00:09:31,905
Yeah, we are.

143
00:09:32,155 --> 00:09:33,156
No, we're not.

144
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:35,742
- Okay, we're not.
- Right.

145
00:09:35,992 --> 00:09:38,370
But we are.

146
00:09:39,662 --> 00:09:43,667
Fine. I just need to know
that you won't tell your sister.

147
00:09:43,917 --> 00:09:47,796
I can promise not to tell her again.

148
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:54,928
Jasmine? We met at Phoebe's
birthday party. I'm Ross Geller.

149
00:09:55,178 --> 00:09:58,139
You did a bad thing!

150
00:09:58,390 --> 00:09:59,849
- Yes, I did.
- Very bad!

151
00:10:00,100 --> 00:10:02,727
- Very bad.
- Very, very bad!

152
00:10:02,977 --> 00:10:04,229
I'm agreeing with you.

153
00:10:04,479 --> 00:10:08,566
Listen, did you happen
to tell Phoebe yet?

154
00:10:09,818 --> 00:10:12,237
Please. Please don't.

155
00:10:12,487 --> 00:10:18,493
I love my girlfriend very much
and I want to work it out with her.

156
00:10:19,077 --> 00:10:20,370
All right.

157
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:22,163
Thank you. Thank you.

158
00:10:22,414 --> 00:10:26,626
But you should talk to my roommate.
I told him, and he knows Phoebe too.

159
00:10:26,876 --> 00:10:29,629
Who's your roommate?

160
00:10:31,131 --> 00:10:36,302
Tell me you didn't tell Rachel about
me and the girl from the copy place.

161
00:10:36,553 --> 00:10:37,887
I'm sorry.

162
00:10:38,138 --> 00:10:41,474
Was I not supposed to?

163
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:04,497
- We're all right.
- It's okay. It's okay.

164
00:11:04,748 --> 00:11:08,918
- We were just waxing our legs.
- Off?

165
00:11:09,377 --> 00:11:13,715
For your information, this is a pain
like no man will ever experience.

166
00:11:13,965 --> 00:11:16,676
Unless you've been kicked in an area...

167
00:11:16,926 --> 00:11:20,347
...that God only meant
to be treated nicely.

168
00:11:20,597 --> 00:11:24,642
Women just have a lower threshold
for pain than men, that's all.

169
00:11:24,893 --> 00:11:27,854
I mean, come on,
it's just a little wax.

170
00:11:28,104 --> 00:11:30,940
Oh, yeah? Come here.

171
00:11:31,524 --> 00:11:34,486
Oh, that's mature.

172
00:11:34,736 --> 00:11:36,571
So now I just pull it off?

173
00:11:36,821 --> 00:11:39,366
That's right.

174
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:46,748
Just talk to me.
Please!

175
00:11:46,998 --> 00:11:50,794
Talk to you?
I can't even look at you right now.

176
00:11:51,044 --> 00:11:53,296
Nothing. Nothing.

177
00:11:53,546 --> 00:11:58,051
- She said it was okay.
- What are they talking about?

178
00:11:58,176 --> 00:12:01,304
- Just get away from me!
- I made a mistake, okay?

179
00:12:01,554 --> 00:12:07,102
A mistake? What were you trying
to put it in? Her purse?

180
00:12:07,936 --> 00:12:11,564
Where did he put it?

181
00:12:13,233 --> 00:12:15,819
You had sex with another woman!

182
00:12:16,069 --> 00:12:17,612
Oh, my God!

183
00:12:17,862 --> 00:12:23,868
I knew something was wrong because
my nails didn't grow at all yesterday.

184
00:12:23,868 --> 00:12:26,871
I guess they had a fight,
and he got drunk...

185
00:12:27,122 --> 00:12:29,708
You guys knew about this
and didn't tell us?

186
00:12:29,958 --> 00:12:32,794
He has sex and we get hit
in our heads!

187
00:12:33,044 --> 00:12:35,505
I want you to leave!
Just get out! Now!

188
00:12:35,755 --> 00:12:38,758
I want to stay and talk about this.

189
00:12:39,009 --> 00:12:42,303
All right. How was she?

190
00:12:46,307 --> 00:12:47,851
- What?
- Was she good?

191
00:12:48,101 --> 00:12:50,687
Don't answer that.

192
00:12:52,439 --> 00:12:57,110
You said you wanted to talk about it.
Let's talk. How was she?

193
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:58,778
- She was...
- Awful.

194
00:12:59,029 --> 00:13:03,658
- She was not good.
- Horrible. Nothing compared to you.

195
00:13:03,992 --> 00:13:06,578
She was different.

196
00:13:08,288 --> 00:13:10,999
Good different?

197
00:13:11,249 --> 00:13:14,002
Nobody likes change.

198
00:13:14,252 --> 00:13:17,255
- Just stop!
- What? Okay! Okay! Okay!

199
00:13:17,505 --> 00:13:18,798
Should we do something?

200
00:13:19,049 --> 00:13:22,761
Yeah. Never cheat on Rachel.

201
00:13:23,428 --> 00:13:27,182
I'm sorry, okay? I'm sorry.
I was disgusted with myself...

202
00:13:27,432 --> 00:13:29,017
...and this morning
I was upset...

203
00:13:29,267 --> 00:13:31,728
...and then I got your
message and I was so happy.

204
00:13:31,978 --> 00:13:34,981
And all I wanted was to get her out
of my apartment...

205
00:13:35,231 --> 00:13:39,736
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!
Wait a minute.

206
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:43,948
What time did your
little friend leave?

207
00:13:46,326 --> 00:13:49,204
Oh, my God. She was there?
She was still there?

208
00:13:49,454 --> 00:13:54,084
She was in there when I was in there?

209
00:13:56,795 --> 00:14:00,215
Listen, the important thing is
she meant nothing to me.

210
00:14:00,465 --> 00:14:05,553
And yet she was worth
jeopardizing our relationship!

211
00:14:05,679 --> 00:14:07,806
I didn't think there was
a relationship.

212
00:14:08,056 --> 00:14:10,350
- We'd broken up.
- We were on a break.

213
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:14,145
That, for all I knew, could last
forever. That is a breakup.

214
00:14:14,396 --> 00:14:16,106
You gonna get out of this
on a technicality?

215
00:14:16,356 --> 00:14:18,650
I'm not trying to "get out"
of anything.

216
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:20,652
I thought our relationship was dead.

217
00:14:20,902 --> 00:14:25,865
Well, you sure had a hell of a time
at the wake.

218
00:14:26,116 --> 00:14:28,743
I don't think we should listen
to this anymore.

219
00:14:28,993 --> 00:14:30,954
What are you doing?
We can't go out.

220
00:14:31,204 --> 00:14:34,958
Why not? I'm hungry.

221
00:14:34,958 --> 00:14:37,627
Because they'll know
we've been listening.

222
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:40,714
God! And to have to hear about it
from Gunther!

223
00:14:40,964 --> 00:14:46,302
I ran all over the place trying
to make sure that didn't happen!

224
00:14:46,928 --> 00:14:50,557
Oh, that is so sweet.

225
00:14:50,682 --> 00:14:55,020
I think I'm falling in love with you
all over again.

226
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:59,274
We can go out. They have
other things to worry about.

227
00:14:59,524 --> 00:15:00,608
We'll be fine.

228
00:15:00,859 --> 00:15:04,320
Rachel, I wanted to tell you.
I thought I should.

229
00:15:04,571 --> 00:15:09,784
And then Chandler and Joey
convinced me not to!

230
00:15:11,870 --> 00:15:16,124
Wax the door shut.
We're never leaving.

231
00:15:16,124 --> 00:15:19,878
It's Phoebe. Someone has to take
my 9:00 with Mr. Rehak...

232
00:15:20,128 --> 00:15:24,674
...because it's 9: 15 now,
and I'm not there.

233
00:15:25,133 --> 00:15:28,511
None of this would've happened
if I didn't think...

234
00:15:28,762 --> 00:15:31,014
...you were having sex with Mark?

235
00:15:31,264 --> 00:15:32,891
All right.

236
00:15:33,141 --> 00:15:39,105
Let's say I had slept with Mark. Would
you have been able to forgive me?

237
00:15:40,148 --> 00:15:43,360
Yes, I would.

238
00:15:44,361 --> 00:15:48,656
You'd be okay if Mark had kissed me,
and been naked with me...

239
00:15:48,907 --> 00:15:51,868
...and made love to me?

240
00:15:54,162 --> 00:15:59,459
If you knew that our hot, sweaty,
writhing bodies were...

241
00:16:03,755 --> 00:16:06,549
I would have been devastated...

242
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:09,386
...but I would still want
to be with you.

243
00:16:09,636 --> 00:16:13,556
Because, I mean, it's you.

244
00:16:23,817 --> 00:16:28,029
Come on, tell me what you're thinking.

245
00:16:29,239 --> 00:16:32,534
I'm thinking...

246
00:16:33,743 --> 00:16:37,205
...I'm gonna order a pizza.

247
00:16:38,915 --> 00:16:41,376
Order a pizza, like...

248
00:16:41,626 --> 00:16:44,879
..."I forgive you"?

249
00:16:48,591 --> 00:16:50,051
Oh, man!

250
00:16:50,301 --> 00:16:52,262
Pizza?

251
00:16:52,512 --> 00:16:55,557
I like pizza.

252
00:16:55,724 --> 00:16:59,436
Put olives on the pizza.

253
00:17:02,939 --> 00:17:06,234
We could eat the wax! It's organic!

254
00:17:06,484 --> 00:17:10,238
Oh, great. Food with hair on it.

255
00:17:10,530 --> 00:17:12,240
No, not the used wax.

256
00:17:12,490 --> 00:17:16,327
Because that would be crazy?

257
00:17:17,787 --> 00:17:21,624
Could I get in on that?
Because I'm kind of hungry myself.

258
00:17:21,875 --> 00:17:23,001
Fine.

259
00:17:23,251 --> 00:17:25,920
Yes, I'd like to order
a large pizza.

260
00:17:26,171 --> 00:17:30,050
- No anchovies.
- With extra anchovies.

261
00:17:30,300 --> 00:17:31,676
That's okay.
I'll pick them off.

262
00:17:31,926 --> 00:17:36,806
And could you chop some up
and put it right in the sauce?

263
00:17:41,978 --> 00:17:44,064
You can have the last piece
if you want.

264
00:17:44,314 --> 00:17:48,693
Well, I should think so.
You slept with someone.

265
00:17:59,746 --> 00:18:02,499
They're gonna get through this,
aren't they?

266
00:18:02,749 --> 00:18:05,543
Yeah. Come on, it's Ross and Rachel.

267
00:18:05,794 --> 00:18:08,254
They've got to.

268
00:18:08,713 --> 00:18:11,591
What if they don't?

269
00:18:14,511 --> 00:18:18,348
You think I need a new walk?

270
00:18:20,183 --> 00:18:21,017
What?

271
00:18:21,267 --> 00:18:25,230
Well, I've been walking
the same way since high school.

272
00:18:25,480 --> 00:18:29,275
You know how some guys walk into
a room and everybody takes notice?

273
00:18:29,526 --> 00:18:32,237
I think I need a take-notice walk.

274
00:18:32,487 --> 00:18:36,116
Are you actually saying these words?

275
00:18:39,577 --> 00:18:43,540
What, now you're not even
talking to me?

276
00:18:44,916 --> 00:18:49,254
Look, Rachel, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry. I was out of my mind.

277
00:18:49,504 --> 00:18:50,880
I thought I'd lost you.

278
00:18:51,131 --> 00:18:54,134
How insane must I have been
to do something like this?

279
00:18:54,384 --> 00:18:59,973
I don't cheat, right?
That's not me. I'm not Joey!

280
00:19:08,857 --> 00:19:12,360
It's 3 a.m. They don't
know that I've come home yet.

281
00:19:12,610 --> 00:19:16,156
You notice how they aren't
wondering where I am?

282
00:19:16,406 --> 00:19:20,785
You know, people can be
so self-involved.

283
00:19:21,036 --> 00:19:25,081
You know what? I'm not the one
that wanted that break.

284
00:19:25,331 --> 00:19:27,917
You're the one that bailed.
You're the one...

285
00:19:28,168 --> 00:19:30,295
...that ran the moment things
got rough.

286
00:19:30,545 --> 00:19:31,671
- That's...
- That's what?

287
00:19:31,921 --> 00:19:34,507
- That is neither here nor there.
- Here we are...

288
00:19:34,758 --> 00:19:36,885
...in a spot again.
What do you want?

289
00:19:37,135 --> 00:19:42,349
How do you want to handle it?
You want to fight for us or bail?

290
00:19:46,728 --> 00:19:51,024
Look, I did a terrible,
stupid, stupid thing, okay?

291
00:19:51,274 --> 00:19:55,028
I'm sorry. I wish I could
take it back, but I can't.

292
00:19:55,278 --> 00:20:00,116
I just can't see us throwing away
something we know is so damn good.

293
00:20:00,367 --> 00:20:04,037
I love you so much.

294
00:20:12,879 --> 00:20:14,964
No, Ross! Don't!

295
00:20:15,215 --> 00:20:18,593
You can't just kiss me and
make it all go away.

296
00:20:18,843 --> 00:20:23,932
It doesn't work that way.
It doesn't just make it better.

297
00:20:27,686 --> 00:20:31,231
I think you should go.

298
00:20:31,231 --> 00:20:32,565
What?

299
00:20:32,816 --> 00:20:36,986
I really think you need to go now.

300
00:20:40,615 --> 00:20:43,910
This morning you said there was
nothing we couldn't work out.

301
00:20:44,160 --> 00:20:45,787
What the hell did I know?

302
00:20:46,037 --> 00:20:49,040
There's got to be a way we
can work past this.

303
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:53,753
I can't imagine my life without you.

304
00:20:56,464 --> 00:20:58,508
Without these arms...

305
00:20:58,758 --> 00:21:01,302
...and your face and heart...

306
00:21:01,553 --> 00:21:05,181
...your good heart, Rach, and...

307
00:21:10,353 --> 00:21:13,940
I can't. You're a totally
different person to me now.

308
00:21:14,190 --> 00:21:19,279
I used to think of you as somebody
that would never, ever hurt me.

309
00:21:19,529 --> 00:21:22,198
Ever.

310
00:21:22,323 --> 00:21:24,576
Now I can't stop picturing
you with her.

311
00:21:24,826 --> 00:21:28,455
I can't. It doesn't matter what you
say or what you do.

312
00:21:28,705 --> 00:21:32,834
It's just changed everything.

313
00:21:33,793 --> 00:21:36,921
Forever.

314
00:21:46,389 --> 00:21:49,434
This can't be it.

315
00:21:53,271 --> 00:21:56,941
Then how come it is?

316
00:22:06,826 --> 00:22:10,163
They've been quiet for a long time.

317
00:22:10,413 --> 00:22:13,041
Maybe she killed him.

318
00:22:15,835 --> 00:22:18,588
Let's go.

319
00:22:44,989 --> 00:22:48,284
Is that your new walk?

320
00:22:51,287 --> 00:22:54,791
I really have to pee.
